## 7. ALTER Script Template

```sql
-- =============================================================================
-- Databricks ALTER Script: {SynapseSchema}.{ObjectName}
-- Generated: {YYYY-MM-DD} | {N}-phase pipeline
-- Target: Unity Catalog table comment + column comments (1024 char limit)
-- UC Target: {uc_catalog}.{uc_schema}.{uc_table}
-- Resolved via: {resolution_method}
-- Classification: {Standard / PII Masked / PII Only / Non-standard}
-- =============================================================================

ALTER TABLE {uc_catalog}.{uc_schema}.{uc_table} SET TBLPROPERTIES (
    'comment' = '{table_comment_max_1024_chars}'
);

ALTER TABLE {uc_catalog}.{uc_schema}.{uc_table} ALTER COLUMN `{ColumnName}` COMMENT '{column_comment_max_1024_chars}';
-- ... one ALTER per column (ALWAYS backtick-quote column names) ...
```

**PII Masked dual-target format** — when classification is `PII Masked`, append a second section:
```sql
-- === Secondary UC Target (PII unmasked) ===
-- UC Target: {pii_catalog}.{pii_schema}.{pii_table}
-- Masked Columns: {col1, col2, ...}
-- Column comments are identical — meaning is the same regardless of masking.

ALTER TABLE {pii_catalog}.{pii_schema}.{pii_table} SET TBLPROPERTIES (
    'comment' = '{table_comment_max_1024_chars}'
);

ALTER TABLE {pii_catalog}.{pii_schema}.{pii_table} ALTER COLUMN `{ColumnName}` COMMENT '{column_comment_max_1024_chars}';
-- ... one ALTER per column (ALWAYS backtick-quote column names, same comments as primary target) ...
```

