### Deploy Report Rules

1. **Always the last file written** — generated only after ALTER execution (Steps E1–E4) finishes
2. **Mandatory for ALL object types** — tables, views, procedures, functions
3. **List every downstream object** in Section 4 with its full `catalog.schema.object` name and type — this gives visibility into the propagation footprint
4. **Counts only for items updated** — list downstream objects individually but do NOT list every column statement; show the counts (e.g., "130/135 cols")
5. **Capture all failures** — even if they were already logged in the ALTER script footer, duplicate them here for a single-file overview
6. **Phase status table** — reflect the actual phases run (or skipped) for this object. Use "SKIPPED" when a phase was not applicable (e.g., no views found in Phase 7), "PARTIAL" when a phase ran but had incomplete results
7. **On rerun** — overwrite the previous `.deploy-report.md` entirely (not append). Each run produces a fresh report

